  <keyword>gammaln</keyword>
  <short_description>Logarithm of gamma function</short_description>
  <syntax>
    <syntax_item>R = gammaln(M)</syntax_item>
  </syntax>
  <param_input>
    <param_input_item>
      <param_name>M</param_name>
      <param_description
      >a real single or real double matrix.</param_description>
    </param_input_item>
  </param_input>
  <param_output>
    <param_output_item>
      <param_name>R</param_name>
      <param_description>result of gammaln function.</param_description>
    </param_output_item>
  </param_output>
  <description>
    <p>The function<b
      >gammaln(A)</b> computes the natural logarithm of the gamma function for a given input<b
      >A</b>, expressed as <b>gammaln(A) = log(gamma(A))</b>.</p>
    <p>It's important to note that A must be a nonnegative real number.</p>
    <p
    >Using gammaln helps prevent potential underflow and overflow issues that might arise if directly computing <b
      >log(gamma(A))</b>.</p>
  </description>
